******
[1] WHO/AFRO
Date: Wed 25 May 2022
Source: WHO/AFRO [edited]
https://twitter.com/WHOAFRO/status/1529444451717742592


DR Congo Ebola situation report
-------------------------------
5 cases (4 confirmed, 1 probable); 5 deceased; 1311 vaccinated
2 health zones affected (Mbandaka & Wangata, [Equateur province])

"This is the DRC's 18th Ebola outbreak and the 3rd to strike Equateur province since 2018. Genetic evidence suggests the latest outbreak was likely triggered by a new introduction of the virus from animals to humans."
(https://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2022/05/news-scan-may-25-2022)

[Byline: Helen Branswell]

